Justification: Fever, ear tugging, lethargy, and decreased appetite are common symptoms of otitis media.  Emily's age and recent exposure to sick children at daycare also support this diagnosis.
Runny nose, lethargy, and decreased appetite are common symptoms of a URI.  Emily's age and recent exposure to sick children at daycare also support this diagnosis.
Fever, lethargy, and decreased appetite are common symptoms of a viral syndrome.  Emily's age and recent exposure to sick children at daycare also support this diagnosis.
